There's a huge amount of speculation in this article, which I need to remove now.[[User:Whophd|Whophd]] ([[User talk:Whophd|talk]]) 05:21, 19 June 2009 (UTC)
==Rumoured content== Information removed from main article on 6 July 2009, due to a violation of [[WP:CRYSTAL]] and no sources provided. Information should be readded when they have been confirmed and sources provided.
Rumoured content includes: * ''[[Weeds]]'' (2005-) * ''[[Curb Your Enthusiasm]]'' (2000-) * ''[[Seinfeld]]'' (1989-1998) * ''[[The Nanny]]'' (1993-1998/99) * ''[[Home Improvement]]'' (1991-1999) * ''[[Pushing Daisies]]'' (2007-2009)
- [[User:Allied45|Allied45]] ([[User talk:Allied45|talk]]) 06:47, 6 July 2009 (UTC)
==Technical Issues== Nine have so far forgotten to tell people they will probably need to rescan for the new channel. :-)
I say that because I've had to rescan their carrier on two quite different DTV devices, one because it couldn't hold a lock on the MPEG stream, the other because it could no longer find the EPG data. This is unlike TEN, SBS and ABC, who were not only able to add and/or rename existing sub-channels without requiring that, but also because Nine hasn't been wild with it's advertising telling people about the new channel and suggesting a rescan if there were problems (ABC did that when they moved ABC2 to LCN 22).
It seems Nine are taking some liberties with reformatting the DVB-T stream prior to the official launch of their new channel. Bad move, Nine. [[User:StaticSan|StaticSan]] ([[User talk:StaticSan|talk]]) 03:28, 7 August 2009 (UTC) : Is this relevant to the article? – [[User:Allied45|Allied45]] ([[User talk:Allied45|talk]]) 01:48, 9 August 2009 (UTC) :: Oh yes, just not as I posted, which is why it's here on the Talk page. But I did find a link about it on a newspaper site and added an appropriate comment to the Launch section. [[User:StaticSan|StaticSan]] ([[User talk:StaticSan|talk]]) 03:13, 10 August 2009 (UTC) ::: OK, that's fine. :) – [[User:Allied45|Allied45]] ([[User talk:Allied45|talk]]) 04:46, 10 August 2009 (UTC) ::It seems someone using the IP 203.48.107.240 (intfw.nine.com.au) is interested in this too (they're in the edit logs altering the section on launch issues)...[[User:AprilHare|AprilHare]] ([[User talk:AprilHare|talk]]) 09:13, 12 August 2009 (UTC) ::: Oh dear. :-) Maybe someone is finding it too embarrassing. [[User:StaticSan|StaticSan]] ([[User talk:StaticSan|talk]]) 03:29, 18 August 2009 (UTC)
==Missing shows== Midday shows like Josie and the Pussycats, Scooby-doo, Where are You! and Marine Boy are not displayed on the Current shows list. Should these be added to the list? Should we add shows like Thunderbirds and Foster's Home for Imaginary Friends which air throughout Kids' WB to this list? Is it appropriate to add all the shows that occur in Kids' WB onto the list, or is this classified under Kids' WB? [[Special:Contributions/58.165.27.239|58.165.27.239]] ([[User talk:58.165.27.239|talk]]) 02:04, 23 September 2009 (UTC)
== Coming soon? ==
Where is/are the reference(s)? I've heard no announcement of the listed shows airing on Go! anytime soon. And if they ''are'' due to be broadcast on Go!, then what date. I'd prefer if there was an additional paragraph added specifying how long "Coming soon" is. --[[Special:Contributions/58.108.11.201|58.108.11.201]] ([[User talk:58.108.11.201|talk]]) 10:31, 13 July 2014 (UTC)
== Page move to proper name ==
As the proper stylising of the channel name is '''GO!''', the article should be moved from "Go! (Australian TV channel)" to '''GO! (Australian TV channel)'''. [[User:Nick Mitchell 98|Nick Mitchell 98]] ([[User talk:Nick Mitchell 98|talk]]) 09:07, 1 May 2015 (UTC)
